    • saveListing

      @PostMapping public Map<String,Object> saveListing(@RequestBody Map<String,Object> req_map)
      Parameters:
      req_map -
      REQUEST METHOD - POST
      { "type" : "DEPARTMENT", "action" : "ADD", "items" : ["Software Engineer", "QA Engineer", "HR Manager"] }
      OR
      { "type" : "DEPARTMENT", "action" : "DELETE", "items" : ["Software Engineer"] }

      Key Sample Data Data Type Constraint Description
      type DEPARTMENT String Mandatory should be valid type - JOB_TITLE, DEPARTMENT, BUSINESS_UNIT, SKILLS, LOCATION
      action ADD String Mandatory ADD or DELETE
      items ["Software Engineer", "QA Engineer", "HR Manager"] List of Strings Mandatory Items to ADD or DELETE to/from the listing
      @apiNote headers
      Header Key Sample Data Data Type Constraint Description
      TOKEN G6G57HfD49HPl String Mandatory user token
      LOGIN_ID admin String Mandatory login id / username

      Returns:
      SUCCESS MESSAGE:
      {"MESSAGE":"Data updated successfully","STATUS":"Success"}
      ERROR MESSAGE:
      {"EXCEPTION":"Request validation failed","MESSAGE":"Invalid listing type from the list (JOB_TITLE, DEPARTMENT, BUSINESS_UNIT, SKILLS)","STATUS":"Error"}
      {"EXCEPTION":"Request validation failed","MESSAGE":"Kindly provide a valid action - ADD or DELETE","STATUS":"Error"}
      {"EXCEPTION":"Invalid Token","MESSAGE":"TOKEN missing in request header","STATUS":"Error"}
      {"EXCEPTION":"Invalid Token","MESSAGE":"Invalid TOKEN for given LOGIN_ID :: admin","STATUS":"Error"}
      See Also:
      • Functionality: This API is used to save listing (create/update)
